   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fa2473f4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Overall discussion\n",
    "\n",
    "Taken together, the figures should show that local sensitivity is not distributed evenly across the HBV parameter set. Some parameters create sharp changes in the objective function under small perturbations, while others leave the objective nearly unchanged. This means that the calibrated optimum is locally steep in some directions and comparatively flat in others.\n",
    "\n",
    "A second important conclusion is that the ranking from the 20% perturbation analysis and the ranking from the full-boundary analysis are not identical. This demonstrates that local sensitivity depends on the scale of perturbation.\n",
    "\n",
    "Finally, the parameter-wise figures should be interpreted not only numerically but also hydrologically. The importance of snow parameters, soil storage parameters, and routing coefficients reflects the role of these processes in shaping the simulated discharge."
   ]
